snippet.textDisplay:
I sent this video to my Italian friend (born and raised in Italy) as a shitpost and she actually gave me legit responses lol She said that Mark's mozzarella was closer to what they have in Italy (consistency wise), though she wasn't sure about him using expired and left out milk. She also said his counting was very nice, but their dancing was "just no" lol she also said she was pretty sure you can't make mozzarella in half an hour. But! She watched the end again and said Mark's cheese was closest taste wise as well, because mozzarella is usually quite bland, except buffalo mozzarella which is made in southern Italy. She said it's always entertaining to see people struggle at making Italian things, but she does enjoy Mark and watching videos like this.

Anyways, those are the transcribed thoughts of my Italian friend lol

snippet.textDisplay: In my Garde Manger class for Culinary school we made cheeses one day. If you were looking for an easy cheese to make I would've gone with Ricotta cheese, it's way easier. Ethan's cheese went wrong because he didn't stretch it enough. The reason your cheese had no flavor is because a good mozzarella cheese sits in a water/salt/milk mixture for a few days before consumption. Proud of you guys though! Cheese making is really hard.
snippet.textOriginal: In my Garde Manger class for Culinary school we made cheeses one day. If you were looking for an easy cheese to make I would've gone with Ricotta cheese, it's way easier.
